1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Every developer knows this feeling...

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Context switching. It's the silent killer of deep work.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:16,000
You're in the zone, then - terminal, browser, Slack, back to code.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
By the time you're back, the thought is gone.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
What if your computer just... helped?

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
[Antigravity IDE - Developer typing getUserData()]

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Meet VibeCat. It's been watching.

8
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:40,000
[VibeCat]: "Hey - I noticed a potential null check
missing on line 47. Want me to add it?"

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
It didn't wait to be asked. It just... noticed.

10
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
[Developer]: "Yeah, go ahead."

11
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:52,000
[Overlay: Analyzing... Planning fix...
Executing... Step 1/2]

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:58,000
guard let user = user else { return nil }

13
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:03,000
[VibeCat]: "Done! Null check added.
Want me to run the tests?"

14
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:07,000
No silence. No mystery. Every step, narrated.

15
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Proactive. Transparent. Yours.

16
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
[Developer]: "Hey, can you find some focus music?"

17
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:25,000
[Overlay: Focusing Chrome... [CDP]
Opening YouTube...]

18
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:32,000
[Overlay: Searching "lo-fi focus music"
Starting playback... [Keyboard: Space]]

19
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Chrome. YouTube. Search. Play.
Four apps, one sentence.

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:48,000
[Chrome opens, YouTube searches,
first result selected, video starts]

21
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:55,000
[VibeCat]: "There you go - lo-fi beats to code by.
I'll keep it going in the background."

22
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:05,000
It didn't open a dialog. It didn't ask for a URL.
It just handled it.

23
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Across every app. Without breaking your flow.

24
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:22,000
[Terminal - Developer just ran 'ls']

25
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:28,000
[VibeCat]: "ls -la would show hidden files
and permissions too - want me to run it?"

26
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
[Developer]: "Do it."

27
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,000
[Overlay: Focusing Terminal... [AX]
Typing command...]

28
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
[Overlay: Focus lost - wrong window]
It missed. That happens. Here's what's different.

29
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:48,000
[Overlay: Retrying... [Attempt 2/3]
Re-focusing Terminal [CDP fallback]]

30
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:55,000
[Overlay: Retyping: ls -la
Executing... Verifying result... [Vision check]]

31
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:00,000
[VibeCat]: "Got it. Notice the dot-files now showing?
There's a .env in there you might want to check."

32
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:05,000
It retried. It verified. It explained.
No crash report, no silent failure.

33
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,000
It fails gracefully. Then it fixes itself.

34
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Under the hood: a native Swift client on macOS
captures your screen and voice.

35
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:26,000
It streams to a Go backend on Cloud Run.
Gemini Live API handles the conversation
and decides when to act.

36
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Five precise navigator tools: text entry, hotkeys,
app focus, URL open, type-and-submit.

37
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Triple-source grounding: Accessibility tree,
Chrome DevTools, and live screenshots.
It doesn't guess. It confirms.

38
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:45,000
[GCP Console: Cloud Run services live]
Deployed on Google Cloud Run.
Always on. Zero cold-start drama.

39
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:55,000
[VibeCat]: "I'll be here when you need me.
Or before you need me."

40
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:00,000
VibeCat - Your Proactive Desktop Companion
github.com/Two-Weeks-Team/vibeCat
Built for the Gemini Live Agent Challenge 2026
